{"lemma": "حافِرٌ", "slug": "حافِرٌ", "root": "ح.ف.ر", "root_slug": "ح-ف-ر", "root_link": "/words/roots/ح-ف-ر", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 2, "pos_tags": ["adj", "noun"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 4}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n8473", "n8483"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D8%A7%D9%81%D9%90%D8%B1%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "hoof", "fa": "سم", "ur": "پا", "tr": "tırnak", "id": "kuku", "bn": "খুর", "es": "pezuña", "fr": "sabot", "de": "Huf", "ru": "копыто", "zh": "蹄"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "hoof, claw"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "hoofprint"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "foot"}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "active participle of حَفَرَ (ḥafara, “to dig”)", "tags": ["active", "form-of", "participle"]}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "The active participle of حَفَرَ (ḥafara, “to dig”)."}, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n8473", "headword_ar": "حافر", "root": "Hfr", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", (A,) inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "muHaAfarapN", "text_ar": "مُحَافَرَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(a jerboa)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "went deep into his hole;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "so deep that he could not be dug out."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["A", "TA"]}, {"entry_id": "n8483", "headword_ar": "حَافرٌ", "root": "Hfr", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Digging: a digger."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "―         -b2-  And hence,] The"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HAfr", "text_ar": "حافر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a beast, ("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daAb~ap", "text_ar": "دَابَّة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", S, K,) i. e., of a horse, or mule, or ass; (TA;) [namely, the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "hoof; a solid hoof;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] as though it dug the ground by reason of the vehemence of its tread upon it; (Msb;) a subst., like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kaAhilN", "text_ar": "كَاهِلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gaAribN", "text_ar": "غَارِبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (TA:) pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HawaAfiru", "text_ar": "حَوَافِرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S, A, K.) ―         -b3-  [Hence, by a synecdoche,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xuf~N", "text_ar": "خُفٌّ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waHaAfirN", "text_ar": "وَحَافِرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Camels and horses."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xf", "text_ar": "خف"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".)"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 601}, {"kind": "text", "text": "―         -b4-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaAfirN", "text_ar": "حَافِرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is also applied to (tropical:)  The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "foot of a man,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, TA,) when it is meant to be characterized as ugly. (TA.) ―         -b5-  ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aln~aqodu Einoda AlHaAfirapi", "text_ar": "النَّقْدُ عِنْدَ الحَافِرَةِ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, A, K,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHaAfiri", "text_ar": "الحَافِرِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (A, K,) is a prov., (S,) meaning, (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The payment in ready money is on the occasion of the first sentence spoken"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Yaakoob, T, * S, K)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "by the seller, when he says"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "“"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I have sold to thee"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "” [such a thing]. (T.) The origin of the saying was this: horses were the most excellent (K) and precious (TA) of the things that they possessed; and they used not to sell them on credit: a man used to say the words above to another; meaning that its hoof should not remove until he received its price: (K:) and he who says"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "End AlHAfrp", "text_ar": "عند الحافرة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(since he makes"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHAfr", "text_ar": "الحافر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "to mean the beast,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ald~aAb~ap", "text_ar": "الدَّابَّة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", itself, and since its use in this sense is frequent without the mention of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*aAt", "text_ar": "ذَات"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[prefixed to it],) subjoins to it the sign ["}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "p", "text_ar": "ة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] of the fem. gender to show that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*aAti AlHaAfiri", "text_ar": "ذَاتِ الحَافِرِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is meant by this name. (TA.) Or they used to say this on the occasion of racing and betting: and the meaning is,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "when the horse's hoof first falls upon the dug ground"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "at the goal"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (Abu-l-'Abbás, Az, K:) ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaAfirapN", "text_ar": "حَافِرَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Abu-l-'Abbás,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaAfirN", "text_ar": "حَافِرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) signifying"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "dug ground;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Abu-l- 'Abbás, K; *)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ground that is dug by a horse's feet;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Har p. 653;) like as one says"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA='N daAfiqN", "text_ar": "مَا=ءٌ دَافِقٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "madofuwqN", "text_ar": "مَدْفُوقٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) Lth says that the saying means, when thou buyest it, thou dost not quit thy place until thou payest ready money. (TA.) This was its origin: then it came to be so often said as to be used with reference to any priority. (K.) ―         -b6-  [Thus,] ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaAfirapN", "text_ar": "حَافِرَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The original state or constitution of a thing; that wherein it was created:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "returning in a thing, so that the end thereof is brought back to its beginning."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.) It is said in the Kur [lxxix. 10],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^ay^in~aA", "text_ar": "اَيِنَّا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lamaroduwduwna fiY AlHaAfirapi", "text_ar": "لَمَرْدُودُونَ فِى الحَافِرَةِ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", i. e., (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Shall we indeed be restored to our first state?"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S:) i. e.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to life?"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Fr:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to the present world, as we were:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IAar:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to our first creation, after our death."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) IAar cites the following verse:"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "EalaY SalaEK wa$ayobK \n                        A^aHaAfirapF\n                      \n                     \n                        maEaA*a A@ll~`hi mino safihK waEaAri"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "meaning (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Shall I return to my first state, wherein I was in my youth,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "when I indulged in amatory conversation, and silly and youthful conduct,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "after hoariness, and baldness of the fore part of my head?"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I beg God to preserve me from lightwittedness and shameful conduct."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] (S.) One says also, ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rajaEa A_ilaY HaAfiratihi", "text_ar": "رَجَعَ اـِلَى حَافِرَتِهِ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (A,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaAfirihi", "text_ar": "حَافِرِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (TA,) (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He became old and decrepit:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, TA:) ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "as though he returned to his first state;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "became in a state of second childishness."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AilotaqawoA faA@qotataluwA Einoda", "text_ar": "اِلْتَقَوْا فَا@قْتَتَلُوا عِنْدَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHaAfirapi", "text_ar": "الحَافِرَةِ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, A, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHaAfiri", "text_ar": "الحَافِرِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A) (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "They met, and fought one another at the first of their meeting."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K.) And ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faEala ka*aA Einoda AlHaAfirapi", "text_ar": "فَعَلَ كَذَا عِنْدَ الحَافِرَةِ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHaAfiri", "text_ar": "الحَافِرِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He did so at the first, without delay."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) And ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rajaEa EalaY HaAfiratihi", "text_ar": "رَجَعَ عَلَى حَافِرَتِهِ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He returned by the way by which he had come:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, S:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "by which he had come forth."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.)"}], "source_refs": ["TA", "S", "A", "K", "Fr", "IAar", "T"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}